Package uniol.apt.analysis.cycles.lts

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ComputeSmallestCycles
    This is an interface for algorithms for computing smallest cycles and parikh vectors, checking if all smallest cycles having the same parikh vector, or having the same or mutually disjoint parikh vectors.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractComputeSmallestCycles
    This is a base class for implementing algorithms against the ComputeSmallestCycles interface
    AllSmallCyclesHavePVOne
    A special-case implementation for checking if all small cycles of a transition system have Parikh vector all one.
    CycleCounterExample
    Datastructure for storing two counterexamples for the module.
    CyclesHaveSameOrMutallyDisjointPVModule
    This module checks whether all smallest cycles of a lts have same or mutually disjoint Parikh vectors
    CyclesHaveSamePVModule
    This module checks whether all smallest cycles of an lts or pn have same Parikh vectors.
    PVsOfSmallestCyclesModule
    This module computes Parikh vectors of smallest cycles of a lts.
    PVwithSequence
    A datastructure for saving a parikh vector and a sequence.
    Weight
    A set of parikh vectors and there sequences.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    ComputeSmallestCyclesAlgorithms
    Factory for ComputeSmallestCycles instances
